Detailed Description

This interface represents a CellML import element.

readonly attribute ConnectionSet cellml_api::CellMLImport::importedConnections

The collection of all connections defined in the import or in components which are imported by the import (and so on) and which involve only the imported component(s) or other components beneath the same imported component(s) in the encapsulation hierarchy.

readonly attribute Model cellml_api::CellMLImport::importedModel

readonly attribute ImportUnitsSet cellml_api::CellMLImport::units

The collection of all <units> elements inside this element.

readonly attribute boolean cellml_api::CellMLImport::wasInstantiated

Returns true if instantiate has previously been called on this import, or false otherwise. Note that a call to fullyInstantiateImports() on a model which is an ancestor of this one in the import tree shall be treated as if it were a call to instantiate() on all imports. A successful asyncInstantiate or instantiateFromText call also causes this to return true.

readonly attribute URI cellml_api::CellMLImport::xlinkHref

The URI in the xlink:href attribute. Changing the URL in the xlinkHref on an instantiated import will cause the import to become uninstantiated. If there are any iterators(of a kind which is required to return elements from more than one model) which were created from the sets prior to changing xlinkHref, an implementation may choose to continue to provide elements from the previously instantiated import. Applications must not rely upon the behaviour of any particular implementation in this case.
